index.pages.section.product.java.message: It can be applied to all applications that run in the JVM environment such as WAS and batch applications.

index.pages.section.product.nodejs.message: Asynchronous transaction analysis allows you to analyze single-threaded flows every 10 seconds to find bottlenecks or error records.

index.pages.section.product.php.message: It is applicable to PHP 8.3 and Alpine Linux. SQL, HTTP calls, and Redis calls on the trace can be viewed.

index.pages.section.product.python.message: It can be applied to major applications such as web frameworks, servers, and batches, and can identify delay sections by tracing DB queries and external calls.

index.pages.section.product.dotnet.message: It monitors .NET-based IIS, console, services, and Windows applications that support .NET Framework 4.6.1.

index.pages.section.product.go.message: The Go API allows you to trace web requests and response transactions, general unit transactions, SQLs, HTTP calls, and more in the Go applications.

index.pages.section.product.server.message: It is applicable to physical servers, clouds, and scale-out environments, and supports monitoring and inventory management for large-scale resources and high-use, high-risk resources.

index.pages.section.product.k8s.message: You can see Kubernetes clusters, nodes, applications, and logs at a glance.

index.pages.section.product.postgresql.message: You can monitor performance metrics and SQLs, locks, and slow SQLs, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.oracle.message: You can monitor performance metrics and SQLs, locks, and parallel query data, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.oraclePro.message: You can monitor performance data up to tens of times per second without any load by directly accessing the memory of the database server.

index.pages.section.product.mysql.message: You can monitor MySQLs, MariaDBs, performance metrics, SQLs, locks, and slow SQLs, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.mssql.message: You can monitor performance metrics and SQLs and locks, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.tibero.message: You can monitor performance metrics and SQLs, locks, and parallel query data, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.cubrid.message: You can monitor performance metrics and SQLs, locks, and parallel query data, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.altibase.message: You can monitor performance metrics and SQLs, locks, and parallel query data, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.redis.message: You can monitor performance metrics, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.mongodb.message: You can monitor performance metrics, and analyze and compare trends.

index.pages.section.product.url.message: From the perspective of end users for running sites, the system can automatically detect connection issues with HTTP status codes.

index.pages.section.product.browser.message: It monitors and analyzes the performance of end-user interactions with the browser applications.

index.pages.section.product.awsCloudWatc.message: It retrieves and stores metrics periodically via the Amazon CloudWatch API.

index.pages.section.product.awsEcs.message: It collects the resource usage for each docker container via the META API and cgroup directory.

index.pages.section.product.awsLog.message: It collects and stores the logs generated from AWS resources and stored in AWS S3 and AWS CloudWatch Log Group.

index.pages.section.product.azure.message: It retrieves and stores metrics periodically via the Azure Monitor API.

index.pages.section.product.ncloud.message: It periodically retrieves and stores metrics through the Naver Cloud Monitoring API.

index.pages.section.product.oci.message: It retrieves and stores metrics periodically via the Oracle Cloud Monitor API.

index.pages.section.product.network.message: By visualizing network communication information of the process, performance analysis and fault identification are possible.

index.pages.section.product.feature.message: It provides an optimized monitoring solution by repackaging existing monitoring products to fit the software to monitor.

index.pages.section.management.account.d.message: Create and manage your account for signing up.

index.pages.section.management.sso.desc.message: Log in easily using one ID and password.

index.pages.section.management.billing.d.message: Get started with a trial version for free and use as much as you need.

index.pages.section.management.project.d.message: The project is a monitoring unit. Let's learn about the project.

index.pages.section.management.organize..message: You can systematically manage organizations, groups, and projects.

index.pages.section.management.maintenan.message: You can pause notifications during the registered work hours.

index.pages.section.management.userbehav.message: You can trace the behaviors of users while working on the project.

index.pages.section.updates.release.desc.message: Get the latest release information quickly.

index.pages.section.reference.openApi.de.message: Monitoring data can be extracted via the open API.

index.pages.section.reference.proxy.desc.message: It can block external network accesses and transmit data to WhaTap via a single channel.

index.pages.section.learn.metrics.desc.message: Metrics are the data collected from monitoring targets.
